// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Model Builder seed — runtime INSERT-IF-MISSING (council v3.12 finding B9).
//
// These nine tables are ADMIN-WRITABLE through the Model Builder tile. They were
// previously seeded via db/data CSVs, whose generated .hdbtabledata carries
// `include_filter: []` — i.e. HDI takes FULL OWNERSHIP of the table content and
// TRUNCATES admin-authored models/criteria/weights/rules on every redeploy.
// The codebase already documents and avoids this exact trap for the restriction
// codelists (srv/lib/restriction-codelists.js) and the prioritisation pack
// attributes (ensurePackAttributes in srv/prioritisation-service.js); this module
// extends the same pattern to the rule-engine configuration.
//
// Contract:
//   • NEVER re-introduce db/data CSVs for these tables.
//   • Insert-if-missing keyed on the fixed seed UUIDs below — existing rows
//     (including admin-edited copies of seed rows) are NEVER touched.
//   • Every insert is captured in ChangeLog (locked rule 3).
//   • Wired in srv/server.js on cds.on('served'), next to the codelist seeding,
//     so rows exist before the first request is served (tests rely on this).
//
// Seed content = byte-for-byte the former CSVs (NSW-RISK-V1 delegation model +
// NSW-PACK-V1 standards parameter pack + TfNSW user types + pre-filters), as
// reviewed in docs/prioritisation/PHASE0-RULE-ENGINE-ANALYSIS.md.
//
// One-time migration: the stale .hdbtabledata/.csv artifacts are listed in
// db/undeploy.json so HDI drops its ownership of these tables on the next
// deploy (their content then equals this seed, which startup re-ensures).
// After that deploy, table content belongs to admins — permanently.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
